        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 11:37PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1136 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southwest of Wellington, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lutie, Quail, Dodson, and Wellington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
